---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Contact">
  <section class="page-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
    <h1>Last stop in the test flow.</h1>
    <p>
      You now have six destinations to click through and compare the experience of loading each page. This final route is built to feel like a simple contact or info page with enough text to appear realistic while still staying lightweight.
    </p>
    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1517048676732-d65bc937f952?auto=format&fit=crop&w=900&q=80" alt="Team member speaking with a client" />
    <p>
      The goal is to make each route feel like a real website section rather than a blank template, giving you a more meaningful way to judge how fast and polished each transition feels.
    </p>
    <a class="link" href="/">Back to home</a>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-card {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 2rem auto 0;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    box-shadow: 0 20px 50px rgba(2, 6, 23, 0.28);
  }

  .eyebrow {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.24em;
    color: #cbd5ff;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 3vw, 2.8rem);
    margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
    color: white;
  }

  p {
    color: #dbe4ff;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 240px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    color: white;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
